title: Readout of National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan’s Meeting with Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister of Singapore Lawrence Wong | The White House
content: National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met today at the White House with Deputy Prime Minister and Finance Minister Lawrence Wong of Singapore.  Mr. Sullivan and Mr. Wong underscored the strength of the U.S.-Singapore Strategic Partnership and reviewed opportunities to expand the relationship, including through additional cooperation with ASEAN and other Indo-Pacific partners.  Mr. Sullivan and Mr. Wong also discussed regional and global issues and shared efforts to develop an Indo-Pacific Economic Framework that advances inclusive and sustainable prosperity.###
